body:
**Is your feature request related to a problem? Please describe 🙏**
Yes. Apologies if this already exists, but I couldn't find a solution anywhere. I'm trying to use instantsearch together with a Docsearch index on my documentation site. Docsearch is working great in the navbar, but in addition to the navbar search present on every page, I would like to have an instant search on just the homepage of the docs site.

**Describe the solution you'd like 🤔**
I need a template that parses the JSON object coming in from the Docsearch API. I had implemented instantsearch on an earlier version of my site using the following code:

```
  const search = instantsearch({
    appId: '{{ site.algolia.application_id }}',
    indexName: '{{ site.algolia.index_name }}',
    apiKey: '{{ site.algolia.search_only_api_key }}'
  });

  const hitTemplate = function (hit) {
    let url = `{{ site.baseurl }}${hit.url}`;
    const title = hit._highlightResult.title.value;
    const content = hit._highlightResult.content.value;

    return `
    <div class="post-item col-12">
      <a class="post-link" href="${url}"><h4>${title}</h4></a>
      <div class="search-article-description">${content}</div>
      <a href="${url}" class="read-more">Read More »</a>
    </div>
  `;
  }

  // Adding searchbar and results widgets
  search.addWidget(
    instantsearch.widgets.searchBox({
      container: '#sidenav-search',
      placeholder: 'Search',
      poweredBy: true
    })
  );

  search.addWidget(
    instantsearch.widgets.hits({
      container: '#search-hits',
      templates: {
        item: hitTemplate
      }
    })
  ); 
```

This worked fine with a standard Algolia index, but Docsearch's API returns a different JSON object than the standard one, so copy-pasting the above code shows no results.

**Describe alternatives you've considered ✨**
I've tried parsing the JSON myself but have been unsuccessful.

**Additional context**
A new sample template for parsing Docsearch results would be incredibly helpful! Right now, with no template my search looks like this :( 

